Review saved. Here's the summary:

**Assessment: FIX FIRST**

Key findings in the worktree's `mux_test.go`:

| Severity | # | Key Issue |
|---|---|---|
| Critical | 1 | `"os"` import regression (only needed by dead code not in upstream) |
| Medium | 3 | `t.Fatalf(body)` format string bug (~64 sites, regression); `io/ioutil` reintroduced after removal; `testFile.Read` returns wrong byte count |
| Low | 3 | `defer resp.Body.Close()` after ReadAll (pre-existing); `t.Fatal` in goroutine (pre-existing); dead `testFile*` types |

The most impactful regression is `t.Fatalf(body)` — the upstream uses `t.Fatal(body)`. If any HTTP response body contains `%` characters, tests will produce garbled output or panic. The `io/ioutil` regression undoes commit `a36a925`.
